narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is very fun and can be a great way to fulfill a language requirement at Yale. Even if not fulfilling a requirement, Czech offers a great way to explore Slavic culture with a TRUE expert. Dr. von Kunes is excellent.
If your interested in czech language, go for it. it's a hard language though, so be prepared to work.
Excellent class. New, fun, different. Tough to get an A but still worth the effort.
I would recommend it to a fellow student but only if they are willing to learn Czech and put in the work. It is a difficult language but Prof. von Kunes teaches it well.
A language class that is a lot of fun. The professor is great and will help you out a lot.
